      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "The main query here is the lack of speed - none of these have any. You'll want a turn of foot in what could be a messy race. SOFT LOVE (5) does have that, albeit she lacks early speed, but she got home well last time behind Gentle Steel and gets in very light. She might only be two lengths off the leader despite being near last. BOSSY NIC (2) ran well fresh over 1100m and is better suited up in trip now. She might look to be a bit more positive. PONDALOWIE (3) did lead once over 1400m but struggled. Her fresh run here was good and Zahra on is a big positive. MOTORSPORTS (8) struggled behind Point Barrow first up but this looks a bit easier and she plummets in the weights as a 3yo against the older horses. EAGLE EXPRESS (6) next best.",
